<div id="outline-container-org2c07c71" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org2c07c71">Emacs Lisp</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2c07c71">
<p>
Emacs lisp a lisp dialect for confguring Emacs.
Much of emacs is written in elisp, with some of it in C.
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org88c8d55" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org88c8d55">Values</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org88c8d55">
<p>
Any value or object has a type. it may not always be readable
</p>

<p>
There are differnt types in elisp
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>String</li>
<li>Numbers (iteger and float)</li>
<li>Con cells</li>
<li>Arrays/vectors</li>
<li>Many more</li>
</ul>

<p>
There are also types that are specific to emacs lisp.
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Buffers</li>
<li>Windows</li>
<li>Frames</li>
<li>Threads</li>
<li>Keymaps</li>
<li>And more</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


